HEADWORD: Intercommunity
<hw>In`ter*com*mu"ni*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>Intercommunication; community of possessions, religion,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In consequence of that <qex>intercommunity</qex> of paganism . . .
